As Mackenzie mentions, "the whole gasket is like a kaleidoscopic image of the first four circles, reflected again and again through an infinite collection of curved mirrors." Which might convince you to do some experiments with kaleidoscopes - if so, you might want to check out &lt;a href="http://maxwelldemon.com/2010/01/25/reflections-in-spheres/"&gt;this recent post at Maxwell's Demon&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Some earlier blog posts on Farey sequences and Ford circles are &lt;a href="http://mathrecreation.blogspot.com/2009/02/farey-ford-fathom.html"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="http://mathrecreation.blogspot.com/2009/02/farey-definition-property-and-algorithm.html"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
